criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of idiopathic PD according to the UK BRAIN BANK criteria;

          -  Age between 18 and 80 years;

          -  Able to walk 25 meters without help or with minimal assistance and sufficient strength
             to remain standing for at least 20 minutes without assistance for patient report;
             Stability of drug therapy for Parkinson's disease for at least 4 weeks before the
             start of the study;

          -  Mini-Mental State Examination> 25/30;

          -  HAM-D (Hamilton Depression Scale) <17.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  comorbidity with other neurological disorders;

          -  heart or orthopedic problems;

          -  Chronic alcohol abuse.
